There are several suspicious processes with sockets open in the memory image:

1. Process ID 4 (System) has a TCP connection open on port 139 to 192.168.0.176.
2. Process ID 880 (svchost.exe) has a TCP connection open on port 1185 to 0.0.0.0.
3. Process ID 1244 (svchost.exe) has a UDP connection open on port 1900 to 127.0.0.1.
4. Process ID 2024 (alg.exe) has a TCP connection open on port 1026 to 127.0.0.1.

These connections could indicate potential suspicious network activity that may require further investigation to determine if they are related to the suspected infection.
